metadata.name: Rebug #468
metadata.description:
A debug view of the underlying particulate algorithm of Atoms' Gaze and Quantum Folly. Refined as a gift for collectors.

Enjoy watching the structures form. Once it's fully rendered you can download a full resolution image of 3508 x 4961 px by ***double clicking/tapping***. At this size the piece is printable at A3 size at 300 dpi. If you're interested in acquiring a signed print please contact @KRANKARTA.

Created on Chrome desktop 103.0 on 2022-08-06 in javascript and GLSL. Results on other browsers/devices may vary.

metadata.name: Updraft #206
metadata.description:
UPDRAFT seeks to reproduce the beauty of tornadoes and other vortices in a minimalist style and simple shapes, thus highlighting the purity of the lines of these fascinating objects.

If the tornado of life scares you, remember that while you will probably be a little shaken and confused on your journey, you will end up at the top of it. That's the beauty of the updraft.

[S] or [Double-Tap] when viewing in full screen to save a 4000x4000 PNG image

Artist: Estienne
August 2022
Made with p5.js
Best viewed on Chrome or Chromium-based browsers

metadata.name: Alien conspiracy #54
metadata.description:
This piece is built entirely on thi.ng/umbrella libraries starting from @toxi's template: 

https://github.com/thi-ng/fxhash-tpl

20 % of the primary proceeds and 50% of the royalties goes to @toxi as a donation in support of the amazing work he is doing.

Keyboard shortcuts

- 2 : 2 x resolution
- 4 : 4 x resolution
- x : download canvas as PNG
- s : download SVG version

metadata.name: alchemy(minima) #65
metadata.description:
alchemy(minima) is the companion collection of its older sister (maxima) which tries to explore on the watercolor-like effects caused by the warps.

it is a free mint to thank the holders of alchemy(maxima) and a few friends and supporters who have been with me thru my journey in genart. Thank you from the bottom of my heart.

From the proceeds of the secondary sales of alchemy(minima),

- 40% will directly go to The Processing Foundation,
- 40% will go to the minter,
- 20% will be used to grow my collection.

Enjoy!
